OL,3,CJustice minister defends civil
OL,4,Cservant's PSNI chief rebuke
OL,6,FThe PSNI Chief constable has defended
OL,7,Fhis lobbying of the Prime Minister and
OL,8,FLondon Government officials for more
OL,9,Fmoney.
OL,11,FJon Boutcher said he has been
OL,12,Fhighlighting financial concerns and
OL,13,Fhis legal obligations and would
OL,14,Fcontinue to work with stakeholders.
OL,16,FJustice Minister Naomi Long said that
OL,17,Fwhile she supported the call for more
OL,18,Ffunding for the police, her official's
OL,19,Fletter was "entirely appropriate".
