OL,6,FMr Widdis states the chief constable
OL,7,Fgoes beyond his remit in terms of both
OL,8,Ffinancial accounting and
OL,9,Fconstitutionally.
OL,11,FHe states it is not the first time the
OL,12,Fchief constable has had to be reminded
OL,13,Fof his position.
OL,15,FThe Police Federation accused the
OL,16,Fcivil servant of a "high-handed
OL,17,Fattempt to gag, embarrass and
OL,18,Fchastise" Mr Boutcher.
