OL,6,FHe added: "It was a shocking insight
OL,7,Finto how a senior civil servant
OL,8,Fregards our chief constable without as
OL,9,Fmuch as a mention of the officers who
OL,10,Fwere injured in street unrest or a
OL,11,Fcredible acceptance of the day-to-day
OL,12,Fstruggle to make ends meet with a
OL,13,Fwholly inadequate budget.
OL,15,F"Policing is on its knees and the
OL,16,Fpleas for positive intervention are
OL,17,Fnot being heeded.
OL,19,F"Mr Boutcher was right to go over the
OL,20,Fheads of local ministers and appeal
OL,21,Fdirectly to the Prime Minister.
